<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<FindBugsFilter xmlns="https://github.com/spotbugs/filter/3.0.0">
  <!--
    Reviewed suppressions (Chapter 16: suppress with a reason, never disable a whole detector).

    This module has NONE: that is the chapter's point made by the build. The metrics registry records
    through AtomicLong / LongAdder / ConcurrentHashMap, the correlation context is a per-thread
    holder, and the log and snapshot records are immutable, so the representation-exposure and
    thread-safety detectors stay quiet without any suppression. The filter is kept (empty) so a
    future, genuinely-reviewed suppression has a home with a reason, rather than being added inline.
  -->
</FindBugsFilter>
